WEBVTT

1
00:00:01.892 --> 00:00:03.728
<i>Previously...</i>.

2
00:00:04.875 --> 00:00:07.110
Where's the real
Harry Vanderspeigle?

3
00:00:07.298 --> 00:00:08.110
I don't know.

4
00:00:08.131 --> 00:00:10.479
Dr. Vanderspeigle.
a new doctor has arrived.

5
00:00:10.500 --> 00:00:13.486
- I'm Dr. Ethan.
- I'm glad you know about me.

6
00:00:13.507 --> 00:00:15.195
No one likes to hide.

7
00:00:15.390 --> 00:00:18.312
Stop blaming yourself
for giving up Jay.

8
00:00:18.484 --> 00:00:20.406
He can take care of himself.

9
00:00:22.031 --> 00:00:23.429
He will die.

10
00:00:23.609 --> 00:00:25.648
Cut off my leg.

11
00:00:26.328 --> 00:00:28.820
<i>If it weren't for Asta.
I'd be dead.

12
00:00:28.921 --> 00:00:31.291
They took your ship. didn't they?

13
00:00:31.312 --> 00:00:36.210
So they're on to you.
It's probably Men in Black.

14
00:00:36.405 --> 00:00:37.876
<i>I invited some friends.</i>

15
00:00:37.897 --> 00:00:39.759
They are Sarah and Richard Houston.

16
00:00:39.780 --> 00:00:42.795
<i>- You can watch Max.
- I'd love to.

17
00:00:43.287 --> 00:00:44.584
<i>You didn't have to take it.</i>

18
00:00:45.608 --> 00:00:47.225
<i>The young will know.</i>

19
00:00:47.311 --> 00:00:50.485
Good. When he goes to warn him.
we'll finally get the alien.

20
00:00:50.506 --> 00:00:52.467
Asta! Are you here!

21
00:01:03.925 --> 00:01:05.729
<i>Everyone must die.</i>

22
00:01:06.300 --> 00:01:10.425
<i>It's the normal life cycle
of all beings in the universe.

23
00:01:11.011 --> 00:01:12.787
<i>Some may live longer.</i>.

24
00:01:12.808 --> 00:01:16.823
<i>but every organism
has a beginning and an end.

25
00:01:23.653 --> 00:01:25.344
<i>Animals know this</i>.

26
00:01:25.707 --> 00:01:28.824
<i>They live in harmony with the Earth.
as commanded.

27
00:01:29.699 --> 00:01:33.121
<i>The people I kill.
they'd die anyway.

28
00:01:33.817 --> 00:01:36.621
<i>At least I'll kill them
for a good reason.

29
00:01:38.691 --> 00:01:40.503
<i>It's different with people.</i>

30
00:01:40.785 --> 00:01:45.300
<i>They kill because they know.
that they are small. insignificant and weak.

31
00:01:45.699 --> 00:01:48.089
<i>Killing makes them feel powerful.</i>

32
00:01:48.996 --> 00:01:50.871
<i>For a while.</i>

33
00:02:06.699 --> 00:02:09.207
Five months ago

34
00:02:13.261 --> 00:02:15.550
INSULINE DR. SAM HODGES
<u>NO</u> FOR PATIENTS

35
00:02:37.622 --> 00:02:39.537
<i>If a man is smart.</i>.

36
00:02:40.548 --> 00:02:43.256
<i>even murder gets away with it.</i>

37
00:02:58.942 --> 00:03:02.451
<i>Of course no being
gets away with anything.

38
00:03:10.323 --> 00:03:12.651
<i>The universe knows what you have done.</i>.

39
00:03:13.019 --> 00:03:15.034
<i>even if no one else.</i>

40
00:03:29.979 --> 00:03:33.480
<i>The universe. one way or another.
will restore balance.

41
00:03:37.086 --> 00:03:38.893
<i>People have a term for it</i>.

42
00:03:40.779 --> 00:03:42.401
<i>They call it karma.</i>

43
00:03:46.178 --> 00:03:49.537
::PROJECT HAVEN::
<i>present:</i>.

44
00:03:53.460 --> 00:03:55.483
Resident Alien [1x10].
<i>"Patience's Heroes"</i>

45
00:03:55.503 --> 00:03:57.382
Polish text:
Power. DRIXER. Krauzerek

46
00:03:59.127 --> 00:04:00.939
You said Asta's car was here.

47
00:04:01.853 --> 00:04:04.104
- Are you calling me a liar?
- If the shoe fits...

48
00:04:04.322 --> 00:04:05.533
Don't argue.

49
00:04:05.554 --> 00:04:08.556
We're all worried. D'arce.
It's a bad situation.

50
00:04:08.577 --> 00:04:11.673
I almost had a heart attack
when you started banging on my door at dawn.

51
00:04:12.076 --> 00:04:15.946
I'm sorry that finding the corpse
of my loved one in the freezer

52
00:04:15.967 --> 00:04:17.873
is so inconvenient for you!

53
00:04:17.975 --> 00:04:20.498
It's about human life. dumbass.

54
00:04:20.698 --> 00:04:22.412
Harry is dead.

55
00:04:25.344 --> 00:04:27.337
What's going on here?

56
00:04:27.540 --> 00:04:29.816
I wonder.
why I got out of bed.

57
00:04:29.837 --> 00:04:31.134
It's a good thing you're alive.

58
00:04:31.251 --> 00:04:33.134
That's not possible.

59
00:04:33.454 --> 00:04:35.743
She's worse than your dog.

60
00:04:36.405 --> 00:04:38.890
I didn't have the heart
to wake Cletus.

61
00:04:39.484 --> 00:04:41.455
He was just chasing goats in his sleep.

62
00:04:41.476 --> 00:04:42.492
I'll go get it.

63
00:04:43.187 --> 00:04:44.432
Sorry. Doc.

64
00:04:44.453 --> 00:04:47.088
but D'arcy broke into your basement yesterday
into your basement

65
00:04:47.109 --> 00:04:49.361
and she thinks she saw
you dead in the freezer.

66
00:04:49.382 --> 00:04:53.014
I told her it was probably
some kind of frozen pig.

67
00:04:53.178 --> 00:04:54.993
I'm more handsome than a pig.

68
00:04:55.014 --> 00:04:58.237
Me too. I'm probably
somewhere between a pig and a dolphin.

69
00:04:58.258 --> 00:05:00.654
Dolphins are awesome.

70
00:05:05.560 --> 00:05:06.786
There's just meat there.

71
00:05:07.091 --> 00:05:09.161
- You moved the body.
- Sure.

72
00:05:09.966 --> 00:05:10.880
You look at them.

73
00:05:10.901 --> 00:05:12.546
I'm talking about a corpse. twit.

74
00:05:12.567 --> 00:05:15.286
We know it wasn't him.
but I saw a dead body downstairs.

75
00:05:16.684 --> 00:05:18.262
Why was Asta's car standing there?

76
00:05:18.543 --> 00:05:20.647
We were together
at a medical conference.

77
00:05:20.668 --> 00:05:22.270
You smell like booze.

78
00:05:22.363 --> 00:05:24.949
You need to go now. D'arce.
I'll buy you breakfast.

79
00:05:24.970 --> 00:05:26.645
No!

80
00:05:27.933 --> 00:05:29.295
I know what I saw.

81
00:05:29.316 --> 00:05:31.621
Stop manipulating me.
I'm not a crazy person.

82
00:05:31.738 --> 00:05:33.136
The deputy said.

83
00:05:34.238 --> 00:05:35.131
that it's time to go.

84
00:05:35.152 --> 00:05:37.316
- No!
- Let's go...

85
00:05:37.337 --> 00:05:39.133
Get your fucking hands off me!

86
00:05:39.837 --> 00:05:40.743
Damn...

87
00:05:41.133 --> 00:05:43.804
<i>Help me. deputy!
She's clinging to me!

88
00:05:45.172 --> 00:05:48.251
<i>I'm sorry I have to kill everyone
and get out of here.

89
00:05:48.696 --> 00:05:51.407
<i>The spring is coming.</i>

90
00:05:56.492 --> 00:05:57.789
<i>Don't tug on my hair!

91
00:05:58.281 --> 00:06:00.588
<i>- Let go of his hair!
- Take...</i>.

92
00:06:00.609 --> 00:06:02.304
<i>D'arcy. leave the chair.

93
00:06:02.913 --> 00:06:03.861
- Yes.
<i>- Here you go!</i>

94
00:06:03.882 --> 00:06:06.501
<i>- You spitting...</i>.
- Quite nice here.

95
00:06:06.522 --> 00:06:08.936
<i>I'll show you what handcuffs are for!</i>

96
00:06:09.014 --> 00:06:11.100
Come on. let's go!

97
00:06:11.233 --> 00:06:13.826
I gotta hand it to you.
you fight like a pack of pitbulls.

98
00:06:14.233 --> 00:06:17.324
Come on! Hit me!
I know you want it. Sheriff!

99
00:06:17.513 --> 00:06:19.071
- Come on!
- Don't struggle!

100
00:06:19.092 --> 00:06:21.110
It's gonna be okay.
I'll take your car.

101
00:06:21.131 --> 00:06:22.209
Get in the car!

102
00:06:22.615 --> 00:06:24.060
Sorry about that. Doc.

103
00:06:24.632 --> 00:06:27.521
I am incredibly pissed off
by this intrusion!

104
00:06:28.927 --> 00:06:30.375
<i>"I will read you your rights."</i>.

105
00:06:30.396 --> 00:06:32.841
<i>Well. now what?

106
00:06:33.549 --> 00:06:34.680
<i>That's the problem!

107
00:06:37.447 --> 00:06:39.736
<i>Good already. good!</i>.

108
00:07:00.026 --> 00:07:01.946
Turn it on. I need to see this.

109
00:07:13.534 --> 00:07:15.488
She stole it.

110
00:07:15.847 --> 00:07:16.957
I knew.

111
00:07:17.058 --> 00:07:19.754
She's the guy in black
with a purple skirt.

112
00:07:21.339 --> 00:07:23.081
Harry needs to be warned.

113
00:07:42.455 --> 00:07:44.040
I said he would lead us.

114
00:07:57.685 --> 00:07:59.978
What's the matter?
I'm worried about you.

115
00:07:59.999 --> 00:08:01.127
You are grossly exaggerating.

116
00:08:01.396 --> 00:08:03.157
You already took me out of jail.

117
00:08:03.178 --> 00:08:05.078
Am I overreacting? Oh. great.

118
00:08:05.099 --> 00:08:08.013
I woke up to hundreds of text messages
and a recording in the mail.

119
00:08:08.034 --> 00:08:09.867
where you scream: "He's dead!

120
00:08:09.888 --> 00:08:11.809
I already know what happened.

121
00:08:12.099 --> 00:08:14.216
You and Harry killed the guy.

122
00:08:14.606 --> 00:08:17.366
It happens. but I'll help you.
We'll drive my car to Canada.

123
00:08:17.387 --> 00:08:19.053
I have a friend from Juneau there.

124
00:08:19.074 --> 00:08:21.920
I have a safe deposit box there.
A thousand bucks is all we need.

125
00:08:21.941 --> 00:08:23.620
Well. and three passports.

126
00:08:25.135 --> 00:08:27.433
That's a lot to digest.

127
00:08:28.034 --> 00:08:30.222
But I didn't kill anyone.

128
00:08:30.824 --> 00:08:31.777
Are you sure?

129
00:08:32.635 --> 00:08:33.941
I would remember.

130
00:08:34.863 --> 00:08:36.347
Bright.

131
00:08:37.652 --> 00:08:39.753
So the sheriff was right.
I'm crazy.

132
00:08:39.995 --> 00:08:42.394
- To fall so low...
- D'arcy. what have you done?

133
00:08:42.886 --> 00:08:47.670
I broke into Harry's last night.
where I saw a freezer full of meat

134
00:08:47.691 --> 00:08:49.487
and I took it for a dead body.

135
00:08:50.901 --> 00:08:53.986
- D'arce. how much did you drink?
- Almost nothing.

136
00:08:54.007 --> 00:08:58.005
I ate some marijuana
and a tablet I found on the sofa.

137
00:08:58.026 --> 00:08:59.104
Come on!

138
00:09:00.181 --> 00:09:03.230
It's obvious that you're keeping
some big secret.

139
00:09:03.251 --> 00:09:06.658
You're my best friend.
I have no secrets from you.

140
00:09:08.016 --> 00:09:09.386
- You're lying.
- No.

141
00:09:09.407 --> 00:09:11.028
- Yes.
- No.

142
00:09:11.172 --> 00:09:12.690
It goes to know you. Remember?

143
00:09:12.711 --> 00:09:15.508
You start hugging all of a sudden.

144
00:09:16.412 --> 00:09:17.641
This is not true.

145
00:09:19.479 --> 00:09:20.776
D'arce. come on.

146
00:09:20.987 --> 00:09:23.745
- Thanks for the bail. I gotta go.
- D'arcy...

147
00:09:28.549 --> 00:09:29.276
Christ...

148
00:09:38.566 --> 00:09:40.579
Slow down. You're too close.

149
00:09:40.600 --> 00:09:42.785
It was like I was riding with my grandmother.

150
00:09:42.972 --> 00:09:45.488
Go to the back. Grandma.
and knit me a sweater.

151
00:09:54.581 --> 00:09:57.169
Great. you distracted me
and now we're losing the bastard.

152
00:09:57.190 --> 00:09:59.588
Christ. Are you okay?

153
00:10:00.573 --> 00:10:02.690
Please be careful with your words.

154
00:10:03.791 --> 00:10:06.198
You owe me a hundred for the bike.

155
00:10:08.554 --> 00:10:09.595
Nothing happened to him.

156
00:10:09.616 --> 00:10:11.632
I'm happy to wait for the police.

157
00:10:12.640 --> 00:10:15.148
Pay the kid.
You made me hit her.

158
00:10:15.741 --> 00:10:16.546
Quick!

159
00:10:17.045 --> 00:10:18.241
We lost it.

160
00:10:20.490 --> 00:10:21.490
My pleasure.

161
00:10:23.294 --> 00:10:25.388
- It took you a long time.
- That's a hundred!

162
00:10:29.474 --> 00:10:31.443
<i>My device
is fully charged.

163
00:10:31.661 --> 00:10:34.429
<i>A single press
and the countdown begins.

164
00:10:34.450 --> 00:10:36.633
<i>And about an hour and a half later</i>.

165
00:10:36.654 --> 00:10:39.177
<i>Eight billion people
will cease to exist.

166
00:10:39.770 --> 00:10:44.465
<i>Then I will accomplish a mission that will forever
will change the course of the history of the universe.

167
00:10:44.486 --> 00:10:46.161
<i>Do you dream of pizza?

168
00:10:46.182 --> 00:10:49.892
<i>Mommy's Pizzeria Now Open
in downtown Patience!

169
00:10:57.260 --> 00:11:00.377
<i>I can't kill all Earthlings
with an empty belly.

170
00:11:31.961 --> 00:11:33.359
Jay works here?

171
00:11:33.851 --> 00:11:35.554
I gave her a part-time job.

172
00:11:36.336 --> 00:11:38.757
Dad. that's rather a bad idea.

173
00:11:38.945 --> 00:11:42.453
You have an alien friend.
and this is a bad idea?

174
00:11:43.976 --> 00:11:45.492
Here he comes. Get lost!

175
00:11:53.196 --> 00:11:56.188
- I see you have a new job.
- Yeah. It's the first day.

176
00:11:56.696 --> 00:11:57.547
Cool.

177
00:11:58.406 --> 00:12:01.102
D'arcy told me
what happened upstairs.

178
00:12:01.546 --> 00:12:05.149
I want to make sure you didn't lose
any fingers or anything.

179
00:12:06.524 --> 00:12:07.320
No.

180
00:12:08.530 --> 00:12:09.539
They are in place!

181
00:12:10.374 --> 00:12:13.476
If you'd like to talk...

182
00:12:14.664 --> 00:12:16.890
about anything. I'll listen to you.

183
00:12:18.255 --> 00:12:20.672
Should I talk to you about you?

184
00:12:25.360 --> 00:12:26.759
- We could...
- No.

185
00:12:26.852 --> 00:12:27.920
Sure.

186
00:12:28.360 --> 00:12:29.524
I'll get back to work now.

187
00:12:29.675 --> 00:12:32.079
Sure. It was good to see you.

188
00:12:36.057 --> 00:12:37.361
- Hi.
- Good.

189
00:12:37.382 --> 00:12:39.088
Good morning. Miss Twelvetrees.

190
00:12:41.963 --> 00:12:43.393
Treat yourself.

191
00:12:43.980 --> 00:12:45.393
I know you know.

192
00:12:50.120 --> 00:12:51.471
And I know that you know.

193
00:12:52.940 --> 00:12:53.940
Does she know?

194
00:12:54.948 --> 00:12:56.745
"She" has a name.

195
00:12:56.924 --> 00:12:58.057
And she knows.

196
00:12:58.534 --> 00:13:00.362
She knows a lot.

197
00:13:03.948 --> 00:13:05.260
We have a problem.

198
00:13:05.854 --> 00:13:07.630
The government is on his trail.

199
00:13:07.651 --> 00:13:09.760
They know that I know who he is.

200
00:13:10.057 --> 00:13:11.861
What to do from where?

201
00:13:11.955 --> 00:13:13.151
Because it's the government!

202
00:13:13.346 --> 00:13:14.768
Please don't be naive.

203
00:13:15.533 --> 00:13:17.557
- Excuse me?
- Excuse me.

204
00:13:18.127 --> 00:13:20.395
Sometimes I talk to adults
as if they were my peers.

205
00:13:20.416 --> 00:13:22.366
because I'm mature for my age.

206
00:13:22.916 --> 00:13:23.931
I'm working on it.

207
00:13:24.119 --> 00:13:27.416
I hid a camera in my room.
They searched my house.

208
00:13:27.437 --> 00:13:31.124
They've returned to their base
and now they're looking for him.

209
00:13:31.319 --> 00:13:33.140
How do you know where they have a base?

210
00:13:34.513 --> 00:13:36.021
We have our ways.

211
00:13:44.827 --> 00:13:46.355
Where is my phone?

212
00:13:58.277 --> 00:14:01.162
<i>I learned from the squirrels.
that when you fill your stomach.

213
00:14:01.183 --> 00:14:04.191
<i>You should take out
as much food as you can.

214
00:14:04.402 --> 00:14:05.802
<i>Thanks to that pile of pizzas.</i>

215
00:14:05.823 --> 00:14:09.487
<i>I can kill everyone
and I'll have enough for many more days.

216
00:14:09.893 --> 00:14:13.673
<i>Now. with a belly bursting
like a garbage bag.

217
00:14:13.995 --> 00:14:16.791
<i>nothing is stopping me
from completing the mission.

218
00:14:23.437 --> 00:14:25.132
I will test it first.

219
00:14:28.240 --> 00:14:29.218
All right.

220
00:14:29.457 --> 00:14:31.488
If anything. I'll be on the treadmill.

221
00:14:32.785 --> 00:14:34.952
Thank you for helping Max
with his homework.

222
00:14:34.973 --> 00:14:35.895
No problem.

223
00:14:35.916 --> 00:14:38.363
I want to be a teacher.
when I get old like you.

224
00:14:40.393 --> 00:14:42.604
I'm not old.
I'm young. okay?

225
00:14:42.625 --> 00:14:44.495
Life doesn't spare me.

226
00:14:45.984 --> 00:14:48.081
You have to live with it.
That's what life is all about.

227
00:14:49.483 --> 00:14:50.495
It's beautiful.

228
00:15:00.518 --> 00:15:04.628
That doesn't make sense.
According to this. the phone is here.

229
00:15:05.108 --> 00:15:07.925
You're tracking the wrong one.
Set up your mom's phone.

230
00:15:08.628 --> 00:15:10.221
This is hers.

231
00:15:10.706 --> 00:15:11.975
It can't be.

232
00:15:12.197 --> 00:15:14.987
I put it under the camper.

233
00:15:26.394 --> 00:15:28.402
Close the front door.
I'll take care of the back.

234
00:15:35.691 --> 00:15:36.777
Fear not.

235
00:15:37.209 --> 00:15:38.724
We need your help.

236
00:15:39.540 --> 00:15:41.407
I'm not giving you the hundred.

237
00:15:58.031 --> 00:16:01.870
<i>My device uses the energy of the Earth.
to send a pulse across the globe.

238
00:16:01.891 --> 00:16:03.633
<i>that will kill all the people.</i>

239
00:16:04.507 --> 00:16:07.116
<i>I can also direct him
to a specific place</i>

240
00:16:07.395 --> 00:16:09.608
<i>and get rid of this body.</i>

241
00:16:14.327 --> 00:16:15.616
Will it hurt?

242
00:16:19.120 --> 00:16:20.319
Is it you again?

243
00:16:21.715 --> 00:16:23.413
You're stalling.

244
00:16:24.522 --> 00:16:26.366
You're afraid to kill them.

245
00:16:26.652 --> 00:16:28.467
Not true.

246
00:16:28.928 --> 00:16:31.217
My race does not feel fear.

247
00:16:31.451 --> 00:16:34.076
Yes. but you're not
one of them anymore.

248
00:16:34.480 --> 00:16:36.662
You have been touched by humanity.

249
00:16:37.754 --> 00:16:39.678
I will not listen to this!

250
00:16:40.489 --> 00:16:43.951
I was going to die of old age with Isabelle.

251
00:16:44.490 --> 00:16:49.318
I even bought a plot of land up north
New York under the most beautiful maple tree.

252
00:16:50.504 --> 00:16:53.051
We were supposed to be together forever.

253
00:16:55.418 --> 00:16:56.731
Do you miss her?

254
00:16:57.296 --> 00:16:59.239
I miss a lot of things.

255
00:17:00.832 --> 00:17:02.423
Behind the five senses.

256
00:17:04.321 --> 00:17:06.503
for driving around aimlessly.

257
00:17:07.819 --> 00:17:09.230
for a taco.

258
00:17:10.947 --> 00:17:13.432
- But I loved Isabelle.
- How do you know?

259
00:17:13.659 --> 00:17:15.675
How do I know that I loved my wife?

260
00:17:16.261 --> 00:17:18.589
How does it feel?

261
00:17:20.456 --> 00:17:23.987
You feel alive.

262
00:17:25.877 --> 00:17:27.791
Like everything you've ever felt.

263
00:17:28.072 --> 00:17:31.110
Joy and anger in the heart

264
00:17:32.068 --> 00:17:33.321
wrapped...

265
00:17:35.273 --> 00:17:36.392
hoping.

266
00:17:37.704 --> 00:17:40.040
The hope that all will be well.

267
00:17:41.618 --> 00:17:43.938
Love makes you...
makes you feel connected to everything.

268
00:17:44.399 --> 00:17:46.823
It's like you're dazed or swimming.

269
00:17:46.844 --> 00:17:48.610
I loved her. too.

270
00:17:48.827 --> 00:17:51.656
You're an asshole.
You don't even know her!

271
00:17:51.750 --> 00:17:52.758
I know.

272
00:17:54.344 --> 00:17:55.937
When she left...

273
00:17:57.062 --> 00:17:58.936
I felt like my heart was sinking.

274
00:17:58.957 --> 00:18:00.233
It's a rejection.

275
00:18:00.819 --> 00:18:01.810
Not love.

276
00:18:01.831 --> 00:18:03.913
Then why the other feelings?

277
00:18:05.430 --> 00:18:07.046
I felt hope.

278
00:18:07.998 --> 00:18:10.131
A bond with everyone

279
00:18:10.623 --> 00:18:11.998
and all.

280
00:18:12.100 --> 00:18:13.905
I used to feel them too.

281
00:18:15.458 --> 00:18:17.022
You took them away from me.

282
00:18:20.919 --> 00:18:21.966
Sorry.

283
00:18:22.997 --> 00:18:28.200
You didn't take Isabelle from me.
You took me away from her when you killed me.

284
00:18:28.470 --> 00:18:29.754
He needs me.

285
00:18:30.863 --> 00:18:34.264
Stop doing that with your eyes.

286
00:18:34.652 --> 00:18:38.007
When you killed me. you also killed her.

287
00:18:38.270 --> 00:18:39.684
- No.
- Yes!

288
00:18:39.785 --> 00:18:41.295
He cries every day.

289
00:18:41.316 --> 00:18:43.193
Not true!

290
00:18:43.214 --> 00:18:45.128
- You broke her heart!
- Stop it! Stop it!

291
00:18:55.138 --> 00:18:57.622
Harry. where are you?

292
00:18:58.037 --> 00:19:00.116
Call me when you've listened.
We need to talk.

293
00:19:00.338 --> 00:19:01.927
How are you. Asta?

294
00:19:03.787 --> 00:19:06.546
I have to leave early. You okay?

295
00:19:06.895 --> 00:19:09.419
Sure. We got a little traffic.
I'll stand guard.

296
00:19:10.967 --> 00:19:11.919
Thank you.

297
00:19:15.609 --> 00:19:17.823
Asta. can you help me?

298
00:19:17.844 --> 00:19:19.633
I need that rigid foot.

299
00:19:19.992 --> 00:19:21.292
- Really?
- Yes.

300
00:19:21.313 --> 00:19:24.617
I found a shoe
and I need to see if it fits.

301
00:19:28.447 --> 00:19:30.751
We may have another murderer.

302
00:19:35.227 --> 00:19:38.876
So in the end
will look like the other one?

303
00:19:40.011 --> 00:19:41.542
Where did you find this shoe?

304
00:19:42.106 --> 00:19:45.604
On the shore near
Dr. Vanderspeigle's cabin.

305
00:19:47.013 --> 00:19:50.315
Where's the real
Harry Vanderspeigle?

306
00:19:51.901 --> 00:19:53.010
I don't know.

307
00:19:53.396 --> 00:19:57.184
<i>I broke into Harry's yesterday.
where I saw a freezer full of meat.

308
00:19:57.205 --> 00:19:58.773
<i>and I took it for a dead body.</i>

309
00:19:58.794 --> 00:20:02.265
This is terrible news.
but we're gonna find out who did it.

310
00:20:02.729 --> 00:20:03.808
Promise.

311
00:20:31.613 --> 00:20:34.231
He has headphones in his ears.
He can't hear anything.

312
00:20:34.419 --> 00:20:36.622
I can shout out the songs.

313
00:20:36.809 --> 00:20:38.890
He'll be here in two seconds!

314
00:20:38.911 --> 00:20:41.577
You don't want to know
what happens to her when you do.

315
00:20:41.598 --> 00:20:44.848
- Tell me. you little punks.
where the alien is. - Why should I?

316
00:20:46.328 --> 00:20:48.442
Because he came
to kill everyone.

317
00:20:55.526 --> 00:20:59.221
If you think I'm afraid
to kill everyone. then you're stupid!

318
00:21:00.223 --> 00:21:03.229
I can push the button
at any time.

319
00:21:05.251 --> 00:21:08.287
If you agree with me.
that I'm right and you're wrong.

320
00:21:08.308 --> 00:21:11.588
then be dead and say nothing.

321
00:21:13.666 --> 00:21:14.775
So cool.

322
00:21:15.955 --> 00:21:17.158
So we agree.

323
00:21:17.458 --> 00:21:20.478
Farewell. one man
in this room.

324
00:21:35.626 --> 00:21:37.243
<i>It's impossible.</i>

325
00:21:38.237 --> 00:21:40.441
<i>This energy does not work for my race.</i>

326
00:21:41.238 --> 00:21:42.363
<i>Was he right?

327
00:21:42.940 --> 00:21:45.238
<i>I'm not my own race anymore?</i>

328
00:21:46.363 --> 00:21:48.808
<i>This means.
that by running the device.</i>

329
00:21:49.298 --> 00:21:51.120
<i>I'll die too.</i>

330
00:21:59.090 --> 00:22:00.390
What are you doing here?

331
00:22:02.085 --> 00:22:03.109
Nothing.

332
00:22:03.202 --> 00:22:05.491
I make up nicknames for everyone
who come in here.

333
00:22:06.225 --> 00:22:08.037
Would you like to sit down. Mr. Shorty?

334
00:22:09.851 --> 00:22:12.452
Great. that means I have to throw them out.

335
00:22:18.146 --> 00:22:23.451
We sat on this bench
during physics truancy.

336
00:22:24.535 --> 00:22:25.662
Right.

337
00:22:28.151 --> 00:22:29.447
When it was.

338
00:22:32.543 --> 00:22:33.744
Are you all right?

339
00:22:37.429 --> 00:22:39.834
I remember being
so happy.

340
00:22:40.264 --> 00:22:42.850
It was right before
I left for Stratton.

341
00:22:43.459 --> 00:22:47.944
I felt like I was about to start living.

342
00:22:52.296 --> 00:22:54.100
You always seem happy.

343
00:22:55.092 --> 00:22:56.311
That's what I like about you.

344
00:22:56.898 --> 00:22:58.491
Everyone likes it.

345
00:23:00.703 --> 00:23:02.124
But I'm not happy.

346
00:23:03.726 --> 00:23:05.528
- Aren't you?
- Are you?

347
00:23:07.829 --> 00:23:11.145
No.
I never really was.

348
00:23:13.590 --> 00:23:17.082
I had the opportunity. but...

349
00:23:17.970 --> 00:23:19.207
didn't work out.

350
00:23:20.488 --> 00:23:22.191
I broke my leg and that was it.

351
00:23:26.307 --> 00:23:27.954
You can be happy.

352
00:23:30.134 --> 00:23:35.532
I'll play a game with you to make up nicknames.
and yours is Miss...

353
00:23:36.431 --> 00:23:37.845
Amazing.

354
00:23:38.351 --> 00:23:39.345
It can be.

355
00:23:41.536 --> 00:23:42.579
You suck at this game.

356
00:23:44.407 --> 00:23:48.239
But it's true. You've been through a lot.

357
00:23:48.607 --> 00:23:49.649
Shut up.

358
00:23:50.204 --> 00:23:52.274
I'm not amazing.

359
00:23:52.525 --> 00:23:55.204
I feel like I haven't accomplished anything.

360
00:23:57.254 --> 00:23:58.641
I wish...

361
00:23:59.964 --> 00:24:01.352
have some meaning.

362
00:24:02.170 --> 00:24:04.633
be important to someone.

363
00:24:06.172 --> 00:24:07.750
I'm bullshitting.

364
00:24:07.775 --> 00:24:09.657
Not true. you are important.

365
00:24:10.243 --> 00:24:13.165
You are smart and funny.

366
00:24:14.829 --> 00:24:16.434
I wish I could be like you.

367
00:24:16.455 --> 00:24:19.103
I'm afraid of practically everything.

368
00:24:19.457 --> 00:24:22.736
When I look at you...

369
00:24:23.343 --> 00:24:24.962
You are not afraid of anything.

370
00:24:26.398 --> 00:24:29.484
It makes me less afraid.

371
00:24:30.191 --> 00:24:31.601
You make me feel better.

372
00:24:35.632 --> 00:24:36.970
- What are you doing?
- I'm sorry.

373
00:24:36.991 --> 00:24:39.001
- I'm married. D'arcy.
- I'm sorry.

374
00:24:39.022 --> 00:24:39.827
Christ.

375
00:24:40.220 --> 00:24:42.189
I'm sorry. I was thinking...

376
00:24:42.210 --> 00:24:44.710
- All right. I gotta go.
- Yeah. sure.

377
00:24:45.382 --> 00:24:47.499
You have to go.

378
00:24:47.520 --> 00:24:48.475
Fuck!

379
00:24:53.686 --> 00:24:56.499
Max. you have to trust me.

380
00:24:56.904 --> 00:25:00.381
He wants to kill everyone.
Tell me who he is.

381
00:25:00.402 --> 00:25:02.029
He doesn't want to kill anyone.

382
00:25:02.208 --> 00:25:04.567
His ship is like an amulet
of the people of Quimbaya.

383
00:25:05.371 --> 00:25:07.293
Max. he wants to kill everyone.

384
00:25:07.590 --> 00:25:09.497
That's not true. He'll listen to me!

385
00:25:12.295 --> 00:25:14.404
What are you doing in my house?

386
00:25:14.992 --> 00:25:16.904
Sarah. what's going on here?

387
00:25:18.798 --> 00:25:19.896
Hi. Love.

388
00:25:20.698 --> 00:25:22.201
Good evening. dearest.

389
00:25:22.732 --> 00:25:24.802
Everything's fine at work.
What's for dinner?

390
00:25:24.823 --> 00:25:25.950
Divorce? Great.

391
00:25:32.309 --> 00:25:34.229
Doors locked? Weird.

392
00:25:34.732 --> 00:25:36.282
<i>Take what you want.</i>

393
00:25:36.303 --> 00:25:37.605
Don't make me use it.

394
00:25:37.630 --> 00:25:39.514
- Christ.
- Don't hurt the children.

395
00:25:40.514 --> 00:25:43.094
Mike. you have to help me.
Some people are in my house.

396
00:25:43.115 --> 00:25:44.974
They threaten my family with guns.

397
00:25:44.995 --> 00:25:46.521
What? Okay. look.

398
00:25:46.669 --> 00:25:49.504
Don't move and don't go inside.
We'll be there in five minutes.

399
00:25:49.529 --> 00:25:51.159
We don't have five minutes.

400
00:25:51.357 --> 00:25:53.732
<i>Don't go inside.</i>
We'll be right there.

401
00:25:54.330 --> 00:25:55.361
Deputy!

402
00:25:55.713 --> 00:25:56.732
Fuck!

403
00:25:58.224 --> 00:25:59.150
Holy shit.

404
00:26:01.628 --> 00:26:02.536
Help.

405
00:26:02.706 --> 00:26:04.099
Let me out of here!

406
00:26:04.259 --> 00:26:06.588
If you touch my baby.
<i>I'll kill you! </i>

407
00:26:07.353 --> 00:26:08.956
Who is it?

408
00:26:09.151 --> 00:26:10.846
Why does he wear a white coat?

409
00:26:12.397 --> 00:26:13.990
Okay. let me tell you.

410
00:26:14.102 --> 00:26:15.584
<i>I swear to God!

411
00:26:17.498 --> 00:26:19.287
Stay away
from my baby!

412
00:26:21.321 --> 00:26:23.497
We have his identity.
Let's get together.

413
00:26:23.596 --> 00:26:26.091
<Don't give up. Max!
- Calm down. that's not what we do.

414
00:26:26.112 --> 00:26:28.052
We do what I say.

415
00:26:35.184 --> 00:26:36.103
Get on the ground!

416
00:27:26.559 --> 00:27:29.399
You guys are like Daredevil
and Black Widow.

417
00:27:35.954 --> 00:27:37.679
Thank you for saving my life.

418
00:27:38.066 --> 00:27:39.088
We have to go.

419
00:27:45.800 --> 00:27:48.214
These situations
don't usually end well.

420
00:27:48.235 --> 00:27:49.450
It could have been worse.

421
00:27:49.597 --> 00:27:52.524
I don't approve.
when civilians take matters into their own hands.

422
00:27:52.549 --> 00:27:55.995
but you've put on quite a
...heroic performance.

423
00:27:56.790 --> 00:27:58.300
We're a good team.

424
00:27:59.495 --> 00:28:00.503
Yes.

425
00:28:04.485 --> 00:28:07.699
You have blood on your shoes.

426
00:28:09.180 --> 00:28:10.492
I will never wash them.

427
00:28:11.561 --> 00:28:12.679
I'm not going to either.

428
00:28:20.343 --> 00:28:21.436
Well. no.

429
00:28:26.718 --> 00:28:27.772
Too much language.

430
00:28:27.793 --> 00:28:29.442
Do you want to shove them down each other's throats?

431
00:28:29.702 --> 00:28:32.283
You guys are disgusting.
You have an upstairs bedroom.

432
00:28:32.304 --> 00:28:33.405
Let me.

433
00:28:42.082 --> 00:28:43.479
How about the newspaper?

434
00:28:44.286 --> 00:28:45.612
Do you want me to add anything?

435
00:28:47.597 --> 00:28:48.995
Asta is my mother.

436
00:28:49.371 --> 00:28:51.276
Yes. and Sheriff Mike is my father.

437
00:28:58.486 --> 00:28:59.705
Holy crap.

438
00:29:01.274 --> 00:29:02.611
You are that child.

439
00:29:04.283 --> 00:29:05.906
No wonder
you didn't know.

440
00:29:05.927 --> 00:29:07.540
She kept it a secret.

441
00:29:11.017 --> 00:29:12.415
Facts.

442
00:29:12.822 --> 00:29:14.048
I don't know what to do.

443
00:29:14.392 --> 00:29:15.785
She is my mother.

444
00:29:15.814 --> 00:29:18.298
and I don't even know
how to behave in front of her.

445
00:29:18.488 --> 00:29:20.399
Not to mention my father.

446
00:29:22.228 --> 00:29:24.235
Well. yeah. Jimmy.

447
00:29:24.595 --> 00:29:25.868
It's twisted.

448
00:29:26.001 --> 00:29:28.017
What am I supposed to say
to someone like that?

449
00:29:28.321 --> 00:29:30.087
I will meet with him.

450
00:29:30.469 --> 00:29:32.964
I can't talk to Asta
or my parents.

451
00:29:32.985 --> 00:29:34.783
I shouldn't even be talking to you.

452
00:29:34.804 --> 00:29:40.188
but I feel like I'm losing my mind
and I need to talk to someone.

453
00:29:42.570 --> 00:29:44.195
You can talk to me.

454
00:29:44.586 --> 00:29:47.101
I can't live here like this.
I can't...

455
00:29:48.711 --> 00:29:50.812
You can't get away from it.

456
00:29:52.195 --> 00:29:54.703
And you are not alone.

457
00:29:55.406 --> 00:29:56.499
I can help you.

458
00:30:02.593 --> 00:30:04.374
Get free onion rings?

459
00:30:05.749 --> 00:30:06.866
That's part of the plan.

460
00:30:12.306 --> 00:30:13.336
Bright.

461
00:30:18.556 --> 00:30:20.345
You killed Harry Vanderspeigle.

462
00:30:22.072 --> 00:30:23.848
No. I didn't.

463
00:30:23.869 --> 00:30:25.103
Don't lie to me.

464
00:30:27.087 --> 00:30:29.230
Okay. I killed him.
but he started it.

465
00:30:29.251 --> 00:30:31.595
Do you have any idea what you've done?

466
00:30:32.376 --> 00:30:35.188
You can't just murder someone.
It doesn't work that way.

467
00:30:35.360 --> 00:30:37.266
People kill themselves all the time.

468
00:30:37.492 --> 00:30:39.594
Someone killed Sam Hodges...

469
00:30:39.615 --> 00:30:42.500
Yeah. and you saw
how it came out of me.

470
00:30:42.672 --> 00:30:45.188
on all of us.
and you did the same.

471
00:30:45.891 --> 00:30:46.875
No.

472
00:30:47.117 --> 00:30:48.705
Goodbye. It's over.

473
00:30:48.726 --> 00:30:51.526
- Adios.
- Don't say that.

474
00:30:51.547 --> 00:30:53.867
- Wait. wait. wait.
- What? What?

475
00:30:54.641 --> 00:30:57.368
Everything's gonna be okay.
Like in that song.

476
00:30:58.161 --> 00:31:01.977
"Child. it will still be simpler."

477
00:31:03.180 --> 00:31:05.167
- Don't...
- Don't touch me!

478
00:31:05.188 --> 00:31:08.159
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.
You can't leave me.

479
00:31:08.578 --> 00:31:10.696
Don't tell me what I can.
and what I can't.

480
00:31:11.280 --> 00:31:14.601
You're starting to fuck
like a typical Earth man.

481
00:31:15.567 --> 00:31:17.195
Don't go. It hurts!

482
00:31:22.225 --> 00:31:23.248
That's you.

483
00:31:24.623 --> 00:31:28.745
It's because of you that I can feel
joy and rage.

484
00:31:29.514 --> 00:31:30.928
Do you want the rage?

485
00:31:32.311 --> 00:31:34.131
Go back to your planet. Harry.

486
00:31:34.482 --> 00:31:36.013
Whoever you are.

487
00:31:36.303 --> 00:31:38.961
whatever you are.
I never want to see you again.

488
00:31:38.982 --> 00:31:41.653
- We are friends.
- I'm not friends with people...

489
00:31:42.367 --> 00:31:45.607
I mean... not with people.
I don't know what you are.

490
00:31:45.628 --> 00:31:48.435
But I know what you are not.
You are not my friend.

491
00:31:54.473 --> 00:31:56.388
I thought...
 you were my friend.

492
00:32:16.603 --> 00:32:18.103
I don't like it.

493
00:32:20.987 --> 00:32:22.821
I don't like this place anymore.

494
00:32:25.114 --> 00:32:28.095
Detonation in 90 minutes...

495
00:32:57.925 --> 00:32:59.667
I'm guessing
that you're my father.

496
00:33:01.018 --> 00:33:02.128
Yes.

497
00:33:03.638 --> 00:33:07.042
If you ever
touch Asta again. I will kill you.

498
00:33:08.984 --> 00:33:10.093
Are you better?

499
00:33:11.765 --> 00:33:14.751
D'Arcy. what are you...
D'arcy. no!

500
00:33:15.654 --> 00:33:16.867
Bitch...

501
00:33:28.233 --> 00:33:31.050
Attention: get out of the way!

502
00:33:35.983 --> 00:33:37.967
Yes. I feel better.

503
00:33:38.881 --> 00:33:40.272
Me too.

504
00:33:41.476 --> 00:33:43.178
We should go now.

505
00:34:01.402 --> 00:34:04.716
Miss Twelvetrees?
This is Max Hawthorne.

506
00:34:04.934 --> 00:34:06.122
<i>You have to help me.</i>

507
00:34:06.208 --> 00:34:09.497
<i>Harry wants to kill everyone.
I think I know where he's going.

508
00:34:23.852 --> 00:34:24.953
Sorry.

509
00:34:25.633 --> 00:34:27.518
Are you the city doctor?

510
00:34:27.539 --> 00:34:28.844
Yes.

511
00:34:29.460 --> 00:34:30.719
A nasty wound...

512
00:34:41.456 --> 00:34:42.660
Urban Physician.

513
00:34:43.339 --> 00:34:44.532
The kid was right.

514
00:34:44.553 --> 00:34:46.638
He's a good-looking alien.

515
00:34:47.028 --> 00:34:50.245
Just be careful. We don't know
what this monster is capable of.

516
00:35:09.363 --> 00:35:11.168
Move. move. move. Let's go.

517
00:35:14.628 --> 00:35:15.941
What is this all about?

518
00:35:20.423 --> 00:35:21.946
I knew you were real.

519
00:35:22.954 --> 00:35:24.292
I delivered an alien to you.

520
00:35:24.524 --> 00:35:27.500
I can finally be done with her.

521
00:35:28.954 --> 00:35:31.055
I'm sorry. but this woman is...

522
00:35:31.664 --> 00:35:33.438
a crazy nutcase.

523
00:35:34.133 --> 00:35:35.591
I completely agree.

524
00:35:35.861 --> 00:35:36.711
Shut up!

525
00:35:39.164 --> 00:35:40.752
Are you guys in black?

526
00:35:40.773 --> 00:35:44.127
Come on. That's not their name.
You've seen a lot of movies.

527
00:35:44.148 --> 00:35:47.969
If I wanted their help.
I'd ask my superiors.

528
00:35:49.218 --> 00:35:51.726
And then we wouldn't have an alien. right?

529
00:35:52.726 --> 00:35:53.588
What kind of us?

530
00:35:53.609 --> 00:35:56.132
It's more complicated
than you think.

531
00:35:56.546 --> 00:35:59.813
Too bad you won't be able to see
how it's gonna play out.

532
00:36:00.140 --> 00:36:01.452
Get rid of it.

533
00:36:02.819 --> 00:36:04.069
I told you.

534
00:36:04.644 --> 00:36:06.265
I have other orders.

535
00:36:14.475 --> 00:36:15.477
I'll kill you later.

536
00:36:29.860 --> 00:36:30.993
I don't understand it.

537
00:36:31.297 --> 00:36:35.219
First Sam. then this pair
of travelers terrorizing people.

538
00:36:35.805 --> 00:36:37.740
Don't get me wrong.
I like chaos.

539
00:36:38.656 --> 00:36:39.789
Very.

540
00:36:40.500 --> 00:36:42.391
Maybe even a little too much.

541
00:36:42.641 --> 00:36:46.406
Yes. it is quite disturbing.

542
00:36:46.875 --> 00:36:49.922
Don't forget the foot
with a matching shoe.

543
00:36:50.569 --> 00:36:54.788
But is all this really
just a coincidence?

544
00:36:55.186 --> 00:36:57.905
- I don't believe in coincidences.
- Neither do I.

545
00:36:58.928 --> 00:37:03.122
Both the shoe and the foot were found
in the same place.

546
00:37:03.143 --> 00:37:04.696
right next door to Dr. Vanderspeigle's house.

547
00:37:04.717 --> 00:37:07.375
You mean the shoe.
the foot and the door handle.

548
00:37:07.396 --> 00:37:10.927
It certainly didn't come
from any houseboat.

549
00:37:11.544 --> 00:37:14.179
Looks like we have
a new prime suspect.

550
00:37:14.200 --> 00:37:16.109
We will visit Dr. Vanderspeigle tomorrow

551
00:37:16.130 --> 00:37:18.044
and we'll find out
if he has anything to add.

552
00:37:21.014 --> 00:37:22.039
What is it?

553
00:37:25.836 --> 00:37:29.836
O... my... God.

554
00:37:30.679 --> 00:37:33.209
- Is that Nespresso?
- It's nothing.

555
00:37:33.230 --> 00:37:35.968
I bought it for the office.
It was on sale.

556
00:37:37.923 --> 00:37:39.691
You bought me a capsule machine.

557
00:37:39.712 --> 00:37:41.738
What are you doing?
I bought it for everyone.

558
00:37:41.759 --> 00:37:43.284
- What are you doing?
- No.

559
00:37:43.578 --> 00:37:48.784
You bought it for me
and you agree with my instincts.

560
00:37:48.805 --> 00:37:52.151
Yes. you have a decent instinct.
But he is for everyone.

561
00:37:52.172 --> 00:37:54.113
Not just for you.
What are you doing?

562
00:37:54.134 --> 00:37:55.773
You bought it for me.

563
00:38:16.786 --> 00:38:17.989
You in the car!

564
00:38:19.093 --> 00:38:20.185
Show your hands!

565
00:38:21.384 --> 00:38:23.794
Detonation in 17 minutes...

566
00:38:37.551 --> 00:38:41.074
<i>I have no choice now.
since my device will destroy me.

567
00:38:42.059 --> 00:38:45.632
<i>I will fly away from here and abandon the device
on this beautiful planet.

568
00:38:45.653 --> 00:38:47.645
<i>to complete the mission.
that I started.

569
00:39:36.244 --> 00:39:38.758
Detonation in 12 minutes...

570
00:39:39.500 --> 00:39:40.914
Split up!

571
00:39:42.411 --> 00:39:43.438
Harry!

572
00:39:48.734 --> 00:39:49.813
There are more of them here!

573
00:39:51.151 --> 00:39:53.051
Freeze! Don't move!

574
00:39:59.328 --> 00:40:00.434
Well. no.

575
00:40:02.131 --> 00:40:03.944
I forgot about the pizzas.

576
00:40:08.990 --> 00:40:10.990
<i>Maybe I can come back and take them.</i>

577
00:40:11.213 --> 00:40:14.396
<i>I will take them on my way into space.</i>

578
00:40:16.899 --> 00:40:19.469
<i>I can't because of this stupid mission.</i>

579
00:40:22.813 --> 00:40:24.617
<i>I'm so hungry.</i>

580
00:40:25.891 --> 00:40:27.813
They look like black ants.

581
00:40:35.523 --> 00:40:37.040
Where is your queen?

582
00:40:44.673 --> 00:40:45.567
Come on.

583
00:40:55.215 --> 00:40:56.208
On your knees.

584
00:40:57.292 --> 00:40:58.723
Harry!

585
00:41:32.383 --> 00:41:34.063
Run. Max! Get down!

586
00:41:43.180 --> 00:41:44.351
Harry...

587
00:41:44.679 --> 00:41:46.288
I know why you are here.

588
00:41:46.828 --> 00:41:49.507
- Please don't do this.
- I have to.

589
00:41:49.999 --> 00:41:52.898
- That's what I came here for.
- I don't care.

590
00:41:53.195 --> 00:41:54.665
You are not the same.

591
00:41:54.959 --> 00:41:57.358
You've changed
since you came here.

592
00:41:57.569 --> 00:41:58.923
since you killed that man.

593
00:41:58.944 --> 00:42:01.727
I've seen it.
I've seen it now.

594
00:42:01.748 --> 00:42:04.208
You could have flown away.
but you stayed to help us.

595
00:42:04.427 --> 00:42:05.998
- You've changed.
- No.

596
00:42:06.887 --> 00:42:09.810
My mission is to kill everyone.

597
00:42:12.185 --> 00:42:15.541
If you kill everyone.
you'll kill me too.

598
00:42:20.932 --> 00:42:23.939
You're right. I have changed. but...

599
00:42:24.267 --> 00:42:25.806
Here's my friend.

600
00:42:27.337 --> 00:42:28.939
Are we friends?

601
00:42:29.916 --> 00:42:31.033
Yes.

602
00:42:31.399 --> 00:42:32.939
We are friends.

603
00:42:35.912 --> 00:42:39.790
Does that mean you'll fly
to my planet with me

604
00:42:39.811 --> 00:42:42.983
and together we will kill
all the Earthlings?

605
00:42:43.498 --> 00:42:45.325
What No.

606
00:42:46.810 --> 00:42:48.584
I'm staying here.

607
00:42:53.583 --> 00:42:56.482
In that case.
I won't kill everyone.

608
00:42:58.850 --> 00:43:00.483
That's a good thing.

609
00:43:03.249 --> 00:43:05.311
I'm gonna miss you
miss you. my friend.

610
00:43:06.163 --> 00:43:07.710
You too. my friend.

611
00:43:09.571 --> 00:43:11.703
I should get rid of
this device.

612
00:43:12.094 --> 00:43:18.057
In 80 seconds. it will detonate
and kill everyone on Earth.

613
00:43:18.078 --> 00:43:20.398
Christ. Yes. Go.

614
00:43:21.460 --> 00:43:22.390
Move!

615
00:43:26.671 --> 00:43:27.898
Just for quick reference...

616
00:43:29.215 --> 00:43:33.512
I left some pizzas in the freezer.

617
00:43:34.629 --> 00:43:36.598
You can take them if you want.

618
00:43:37.145 --> 00:43:38.176
Thank you.

619
00:43:38.699 --> 00:43:39.597
Now go!

620
00:44:12.548 --> 00:44:15.072
<i>Everyone must die someday.</i>

621
00:44:15.650 --> 00:44:19.470
<i>What matters are the choices
that we make in our lifetime.

622
00:44:20.150 --> 00:44:23.145
<i>Killing someone will make a person
feel strong for a moment.

623
00:44:23.166 --> 00:44:25.283
<i>but I realized.</i>

624
00:44:25.447 --> 00:44:28.668
<i>that the real power
is the choice not to kill.

625
00:44:29.048 --> 00:44:33.470
<i>Maybe being human is
is to choose love over murder.

626
00:44:36.850 --> 00:44:40.494
<i>But with love comes pain.
that I feel inside me.

627
00:44:40.986 --> 00:44:42.595
<i>I have to go home.</i>

628
00:44:42.837 --> 00:44:44.879
<i>I hope that the further
I get away from them.

629
00:44:44.900 --> 00:44:46.924
<i>the less I will care about them.</i>

630
00:44:47.303 --> 00:44:49.712
<i>I will finally have peace again.</i>

631
00:44:53.125 --> 00:44:54.336
Hi.

632
00:44:54.930 --> 00:44:57.141
Will you drive me home?

633
00:44:57.839 --> 00:44:59.422
That's some kind of balls!

634
00:45:02.925 --> 00:45:06.816
Thank you for the season we spent together.
Power. DRIXER. Krauzerek. peciaq

635
00:45:06.836 --> 00:45:08.744
To be read in the next one!

636
00:45:08.765 --> 00:45:11.628
